msgstr ""
"Kept server-side only — used to verify each form submission directly with "
"Cloudflare before it is accepted."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:463
msgid "Email driver"
msgstr "Email driver"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:471
msgid "Artwork submissions address"
msgstr "Artwork submissions address"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:472
msgid "Artists send artwork to this address — e.g. submit@agnosis.art"
msgstr "Artists send artwork to this address — e.g. submit@agnosis.art"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:476
msgid "Biography submissions address"
msgstr "Biography submissions address"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:477
msgid "Artists send biography updates to this address — e.g. bio@agnosis.art"
msgstr "Artists send biography updates to this address — e.g. bio@agnosis.art"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:481
msgid "Event submissions address"
msgstr "Event submissions address"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:482
msgid ""
"Artists send event announcements to this address — e.g. event@agnosis.art"
msgstr ""
"Artists send event announcements to this address — e.g. event@agnosis.art"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:486
msgid "Replace artwork address"
msgstr "Replace artwork address"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:487
msgid ""
"Artist sends a new version of an existing artwork. Subject must match the "
"original title. Bypasses duplicate detection — e.g. replace@agnosis.art"
msgstr ""
"Artist sends a new version of an existing artwork. Subject must match the "
"original title. Bypasses duplicate detection — e.g. replace@agnosis.art"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:491
msgid "Removal request address"
msgstr "Removal request address"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:492
msgid ""
"Artist requests takedown of an existing artwork. Subject must match the "
"title. Moves the post to draft pending admin review — e.g. remove@agnosis.art"
msgstr ""
"Artist requests takedown of an existing artwork. Subject must match the "
"title. Moves the post to draft pending admin review — e.g. remove@agnosis.art"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:496
msgid "Promote artwork address"
msgstr "Promote artwork address"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:497
msgid ""
"Artist sends an email here (subject = exact artwork title) to choose which "
"artwork represents them in the shared community gallery on the main site — "
"not their own subdomain, which already shows everything they've published. "
"Any previously featured artwork is automatically demoted — e.g. "
"promote@agnosis.art"
msgstr ""
"Artist sends an email here (subject = exact artwork title) to choose which "
"artwork represents them in the shared community gallery on the main site — "
"not their own subdomain, which already shows everything they've published. "
"Any previously featured artwork is automatically demoted — e.g. "
"promote@agnosis.art"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:501
msgid "Photo-only address"
msgstr "Photo-only address"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:502
msgid ""
"Opt-out lane for photographers and lens-based artists whose photograph is "
"the artwork, not a snapshot of it. Submissions here are published with the "
"original image exactly as sent — AI enhancement is skipped and the quality-"
"rejection gate is bypassed. AI description (title, tags, alt text) still "
"runs. Use the [Photo] subject indicator as a fallback for mail clients that "
"do not support To: aliases — e.g. photo@agnosis.art"
msgstr ""
"Opt-out lane for photographers and lens-based artists whose photograph is "
"the artwork, not a snapshot of it. Submissions here are published with the "
"original image exactly as sent — AI enhancement is skipped and the quality-"
"rejection gate is bypassed. AI description (title, tags, alt text) still "
"runs. Use the [Photo] subject indicator as a fallback for mail clients that "
"do not support To: aliases — e.g. photo@agnosis.art"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:506
msgid "Pure address (no AI at all)"
msgstr "Pure address (no AI at all)"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:507
msgid ""
"Strictest opt-out lane: nothing sent here is touched by AI — no enhancement, "
"no vision description, no rewriting. The published post title, body, and "
"translated-title subtitle are taken verbatim from the artist's own subject "
"and message text; the attached file(s) are published exactly as sent. The "
"quality-rejection gate is bypassed, same as Photo-only. Use the [Pure] "
"subject indicator as a fallback for mail clients that do not support To: "
"aliases — e.g. pure@agnosis.art"
msgstr ""
"Strictest opt-out lane: nothing sent here is touched by AI — no enhancement, "
"no vision description, no rewriting. The published post title, body, and "
"translated-title subtitle are taken verbatim from the artist's own subject "
"and message text; the attached file(s) are published exactly as sent. The "
"quality-rejection gate is bypassed, same as Photo-only. Use the [Pure] "
"subject indicator as a fallback for mail clients that do not support To: "
"aliases — e.g. pure@agnosis.art"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:511
msgid "Goodbye / self-removal address"
msgstr "Goodbye / self-removal address"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:512
msgid ""
"Artist emails here (any subject, no attachment needed) to request account "
"deletion. A confirmation link is emailed back before anything is deleted — e."
"g. goodbye@agnosis.art"
msgstr ""
"Artist emails here (any subject, no attachment needed) to request account "
"deletion. A confirmation link is emailed back before anything is deleted — e."
"g. goodbye@agnosis.art"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:516
msgid "Community announcement address"
msgstr "Community announcement address"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:517
msgid ""
"Any active artist emails here (any subject, no attachment needed) to send a "
"message to every other community member — e.g. community@agnosis.art. Never "
"processed as a submission and never becomes a post: each recipient gets the "
"subject and message translated into their own language, with the sender's "
"name and email included so they can reply directly. Sent from the address "
"configured under Settings → Community → Rules, which can be different from "
"this one. Only works for a message sent by an active, admitted artist."
msgstr ""
"Any active artist emails here (any subject, no attachment needed) to send a "
"message to every other community member — e.g. community@agnosis.art. Never "
"processed as a submission and never becomes a post: each recipient gets the "
"subject and message translated into their own language, with the sender's "
"name and email included so they can reply directly. Sent from the address "
"configured under Settings → Community → Rules, which can be different from "
"this one. Only works for a message sent by an active, admitted artist."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:523
msgid "IMAP host"
msgstr "IMAP host"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:524
msgid "e.g. imap.yourhost.com"
msgstr "e.g. imap.yourhost.com"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:528
msgid "IMAP port"
msgstr "IMAP port"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:535
msgid "Use SSL"
msgstr "Use SSL"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:543
msgid "Skip SSL certificate validation"
msgstr "Skip SSL certificate validation"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:548
msgid ""
"⚠ Use only as a temporary workaround when your mail server's certificate is "
"not yet trusted (e.g. Plesk self-signed cert before Let's Encrypt is applied "
"to the mail daemon). Disable this once the mail server presents a valid "
"certificate."
msgstr ""
"⚠ Use only as a temporary workaround when your mail server's certificate is "
"not yet trusted (e.g. Plesk self-signed cert before Let's Encrypt is applied "
"to the mail daemon). Disable this once the mail server presents a valid "
"certificate."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:552
msgid "IMAP username"
msgstr "IMAP username"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:553
msgid ""
"Login username for the IMAP account — typically the catch-all mailbox "
"address."
msgstr ""
"Login username for the IMAP account — typically the catch-all mailbox "
"address."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:557
msgid "Submission email password"
msgstr "Submission email password"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:563
msgid "Webhook secret"
msgstr "Webhook secret"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:564
msgid ""
"HMAC secret shared with your webhook provider (Mailgun, SendGrid…). Used for "
"both the inbound-mail endpoint (/wp-json/agnosis/v1/email/inbound) and the "
"bounce/complaint events endpoint (/wp-json/agnosis/v1/email/events) — point "
"your provider's bounce/spam-complaint webhook at the latter to keep your "
"subscriber and artist addresses clean."
msgstr ""
"HMAC secret shared with your webhook provider (Mailgun, SendGrid…). Used for "
"both the inbound-mail endpoint (/wp-json/agnosis/v1/email/inbound) and the "
"bounce/complaint events endpoint (/wp-json/agnosis/v1/email/events) — point "
"your provider's bounce/spam-complaint webhook at the latter to keep your "
"subscriber and artist addresses clean."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:570
msgid "Inbox retention (days)"
msgstr "Inbox retention (days)"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:576
msgid ""
"Seen IMAP messages and processed/failed queue rows older than this are "
"permanently deleted by the daily cleanup. Default: 7 days."
msgstr ""
"Seen IMAP messages and processed/failed queue rows older than this are "
"permanently deleted by the daily cleanup. Default: 7 days."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:580
msgid "Contact message retention (days)"
msgstr "Contact message retention (days)"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:586
msgid ""
"Visitor-to-artist contact messages (sent or rejected) older than this are "
"permanently deleted by the daily cleanup. The visitor's IP address is "
"cleared independently after 30 days regardless of this setting, once it's no "
"longer useful for abuse investigation. Default: 90 days."
msgstr ""
"Visitor-to-artist contact messages (sent or rejected) older than this are "
"permanently deleted by the daily cleanup. The visitor's IP address is "
"cleared independently after 30 days regardless of this setting, once it's no "
"longer useful for abuse investigation. Default: 90 days."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:592
msgid "Per-sender hourly submission limit"
msgstr "Per-sender hourly submission limit"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:599
msgid ""
"Maximum submissions accepted from a single artist per hour, across both IMAP "
"and webhook intake. Exceeding this limit silently drops the message (no "
"retry from ESPs). Default: 5."
msgstr ""
"Maximum submissions accepted from a single artist per hour, across both IMAP "
"and webhook intake. Exceeding this limit silently drops the message (no "
"retry from ESPs). Default: 5."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:604
msgid "Per-artist contact limit"
msgstr "Per-artist contact limit"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:611
msgid ""
"Maximum messages the same visitor (by email address) can send to a single "
"artist within the window below — applies across every language version of "
"that artist's page. Default: 2."
msgstr ""
"Maximum messages the same visitor (by email address) can send to a single "
"artist within the window below — applies across every language version of "
"that artist's page. Default: 2."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:615
msgid "Per-artist contact limit window (hours)"
msgstr "Per-artist contact limit window (hours)"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:622
msgid ""
"Time window, in hours, the per-artist contact limit above applies over. Also "
"controls how long a visitor sees the \"already contacted\" notice instead of "
"the form after messaging an artist. Default: 1 (one hour)."
msgstr ""
"Time window, in hours, the per-artist contact limit above applies over. Also "
"controls how long a visitor sees the \"already contacted\" notice instead of "
"the form after messaging an artist. Default: 1 (one hour)."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:627
msgid "Require SPF/DKIM authentication"
msgstr "Require SPF/DKIM authentication"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:630
msgid ""
"When enabled, intake messages must pass SPF or DKIM authentication (via the "
"Authentication-Results header). Prevents spoofed From: addresses. Requires "
"your ESP to include Authentication-Results headers and your domain to have "
"SPF/DKIM records configured. Leave off if you are not sure — rejected "
"legitimate mail is silent. Default: off."
msgstr ""
"When enabled, intake messages must pass SPF or DKIM authentication (via the "
"Authentication-Results header). Prevents spoofed From: addresses. Requires "
"your ESP to include Authentication-Results headers and your domain to have "
"SPF/DKIM records configured. Leave off if you are not sure — rejected "
"legitimate mail is silent. Default: off."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:636
msgid "Description provider"
msgstr "Description provider"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:644
msgid ""
"Analyzes the artwork image and writes the title, body, tags and alt text. "
"WordPress AI Services delegates to whichever provider the site has "
"configured via the AI Services plugin."
msgstr ""
"Analyzes the artwork image and writes the title, body, tags and alt text. "
"WordPress AI Services delegates to whichever provider the site has "
"configured via the AI Services plugin."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:648
msgid "OpenAI vision model"
msgstr "OpenAI vision model"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:650
msgid ""
"Model used for artwork description when OpenAI is the description provider. "
"Must support vision input."
msgstr ""
"Model used for artwork description when OpenAI is the description provider. "
"Must support vision input."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:654
msgid "Anthropic model"
msgstr "Anthropic model"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:656
msgid ""
"Model used for artwork description when Anthropic is the description "
"provider. Must support vision input."
msgstr ""
"Model used for artwork description when Anthropic is the description "
"provider. Must support vision input."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:660
msgid "Vision image max width (px)"
msgstr "Vision image max width (px)"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:666
msgid ""
"Images are downscaled proportionally to this width before being sent to the "
"AI for description — vision token cost scales with resolution, and a "
"description task needs far fewer pixels than the original photo. Applies to "
"artwork photo uploads, rasterised PDF pages, and video poster frames alike. "
"Set to 0 to always send full-resolution images (uses more tokens, no quality "
"difference for typical description tasks). Requires the Imagick PHP "
"extension; images are sent at their original size regardless of this setting "
"when it is unavailable. Default: 800."
msgstr ""
"Images are downscaled proportionally to this width before being sent to the "
"AI for description — vision token cost scales with resolution, and a "
"description task needs far fewer pixels than the original photo. Applies to "
"artwork photo uploads, rasterized PDF pages, and video poster frames alike. "
"Set to 0 to always send full-resolution images (uses more tokens, no quality "
"difference for typical description tasks). Requires the Imagick PHP "
"extension; images are sent at their original size regardless of this setting "
"when it is unavailable. Default: 800."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:672
msgid "Enhancement provider"
msgstr "Enhancement provider"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:675
msgid "Auto (OpenAI if key is set)"
msgstr "Auto (OpenAI if key is set)"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:677
msgid "Disabled — use original image"
msgstr "Disabled — use original image"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:680
msgid ""
"Enhances the artwork image before publishing. Uses OpenAI gpt-image-1. Set "
"to Disabled to skip enhancement and publish the original."
msgstr ""
"Enhances the artwork image before publishing. Uses OpenAI gpt-image-1. Set "
"to Disabled to skip enhancement and publish the original."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:684
msgid "OpenAI image model"
msgstr "OpenAI image model"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:686
msgid ""
"Model used for image enhancement when OpenAI is the enhancement provider."
msgstr ""
"Model used for image enhancement when OpenAI is the enhancement provider."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:692
msgid "Polish biography with AI"
msgstr "Polish biography with AI"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:695
msgid ""
"When enabled, biography submissions are passed through the AI to fix "
"spelling and make minor text improvements before saving."
msgstr ""
"When enabled, biography submissions are passed through the AI to fix "
"spelling and make minor text improvements before saving."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:699
msgid "Polish events with AI"
msgstr "Polish events with AI"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:702
msgid ""
"When enabled, event submissions are passed through the AI to fix spelling "
"and make minor text improvements before saving."
msgstr ""
"When enabled, event submissions are passed through the AI to fix spelling "
"and make minor text improvements before saving."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:708
msgid "Merge biography updates with AI"
msgstr "Merge biography updates with AI"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:711
msgid ""
"When enabled, biography updates are merged with the existing biography using "
"AI — new information is integrated rather than replacing everything. "
"Recommended: artists can send incremental updates (\"I just won an award\") "
"without resubmitting their full bio. Disable to always replace the biography "
"with the latest submission."
msgstr ""
"When enabled, biography updates are merged with the existing biography using "
"AI — new information is integrated rather than replacing everything. "
"Recommended: artists can send incremental updates (\"I just won an award\") "
"without resubmitting their full bio. Disable to always replace the biography "
"with the latest submission."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:717
msgid "Rejection threshold (quality score)"
msgstr "Rejection threshold (quality score)"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:725
msgid ""
"Photos scoring at or below this value (1–10) are automatically rejected — "
"the artist receives a friendly email explaining the issue and is invited to "
"resubmit. Score 0 disables automatic rejection. Must be lower than the "
"enhancement threshold. Default: 3."
msgstr ""
"Photos scoring at or below this value (1–10) are automatically rejected — "
"the artist receives a friendly email explaining the issue and is invited to "
"resubmit. Score 0 disables automatic rejection. Must be lower than the "
"enhancement threshold. Default: 3."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:730
msgid "Enhancement threshold (quality score)"
msgstr "Enhancement threshold (quality score)"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:738
msgid ""
"Photos scoring below this value (1–10) are automatically enhanced. Score 10 "
"= perfect photograph, 1 = technically unusable. Default: 7 — only visibly "
"problematic photos are processed. Set to 1 to disable automatic enhancement "
"entirely."
msgstr ""
"Photos scoring below this value (1–10) are automatically enhanced. Score 10 "
"= perfect photograph, 1 = technically unusable. Default: 7 — only visibly "
"problematic photos are processed. Set to 1 to disable automatic enhancement "
"entirely."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:744
msgid "OpenAI API key"
msgstr "OpenAI API key"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:747
msgid "Required when OpenAI is the description or enhancement provider."
msgstr "Required when OpenAI is the description or enhancement provider."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:751
msgid "Anthropic API key"
msgstr "Anthropic API key"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:754
msgid "Required when Anthropic is the description provider."
msgstr "Required when Anthropic is the description provider."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:760
msgid "Artwork display width (px)"
msgstr "Artwork display width (px)"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:766
msgid ""
"Width of the agnosis-artwork image size used in post content and lightbox. "
"Height scales proportionally. Default: 1920. Existing images need to be "
"regenerated after changing this value."
msgstr ""
"Width of the agnosis-artwork image size used in post content and lightbox. "
"Height scales proportionally. Default: 1920. Existing images need to be "
"regenerated after changing this value."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:770
msgid "Thumbnail size (px)"
msgstr "Thumbnail size (px)"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:776
msgid ""
"Side length of the square agnosis-thumb size used in submission cards and "
"dashboard. Default: 512. Existing images need to be regenerated after "
"changing this value."
msgstr ""
"Side length of the square agnosis-thumb size used in submission cards and "
"dashboard. Default: 512. Existing images need to be regenerated after "
"changing this value."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:780
msgid "Email image width (px)"
msgstr "Email image width (px)"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:786
msgid ""
"Width of the agnosis-email size used in artist notification emails. Height "
"scales proportionally — no cropping. Default: 420. Existing images need to "
"be regenerated after changing this value."
msgstr ""
"Width of the agnosis-email size used in artist notification emails. Height "
"scales proportionally — no cropping. Default: 420. Existing images need to "
"be regenerated after changing this value."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:792
msgid "Gallery overview — items per page"
msgstr "Gallery overview — items per page"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:798
msgid ""
"How many artwork cards the gallery overview shows per page. Pool is built "
"proportionally across all artists; featured artworks are preferred. Default: "
"12."
msgstr ""
"How many artwork cards the gallery overview shows per page. Pool is built "
"proportionally across all artists; featured artworks are preferred. Default: "
"12."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:804
msgid "Review link expiry (days)"
msgstr "Review link expiry (days)"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:810
msgid ""
"How long the Approve & Publish / Discard links in a submission review email "
"stay valid before an artist has to log in to manage the item instead. "
"Applies uniformly to artwork, biography, and event drafts. Default: 7."
msgstr ""
"How long the Approve & Publish / Discard links in a submission review email "
"stay valid before an artist has to log in to manage the item instead. "
"Applies uniformly to artwork, biography, and event drafts. Default: 7."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:816
msgid "System prompt"
msgstr "System prompt"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:822
msgid ""
"Sent to the AI as the system instruction. Use {tag_count} and {excerpt_words}"
" as tokens — they are replaced with the values below."
msgstr ""
"Sent to the AI as the system instruction. Use {tag_count} and {excerpt_words}"
" as tokens — they are replaced with the values below."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:826
msgid "Artist prompt template"
msgstr "Artist prompt template"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:832
msgid ""
"User message sent alongside the artwork image. Use {artist_prompt} where the "
"artist's own description should appear."
msgstr ""
"User message sent alongside the artwork image. Use {artist_prompt} where the "
"artist's own description should appear."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:836
msgid "Enhancement instructions"
msgstr "Enhancement instructions"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:842
msgid ""
"Instructions passed to the image enhancement provider. The AI-generated "
"artwork description is appended automatically as context."
msgstr ""
"Instructions passed to the image enhancement provider. The AI-generated "
"artwork description is appended automatically as context."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:846
msgid "Number of tags"
msgstr "Number of tags"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:852
msgid ""
"How many tags the AI should generate per artwork. Referenced as {tag_count} "
"in the system prompt."
msgstr ""
"How many tags the AI should generate per artwork. Referenced as {tag_count} "
"in the system prompt."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:856
msgid "Excerpt word limit"
msgstr "Excerpt word limit"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:862
msgid ""
"Maximum words for the one-sentence excerpt. Referenced as {excerpt_words} in "
"the system prompt."
msgstr ""
"Maximum words for the one-sentence excerpt. Referenced as {excerpt_words} in "
"the system prompt."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:875
msgid "Trust all admitted artists (skip link review entirely)"
msgstr "Trust all admitted artists (skip link review entirely)"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:880
msgid ""
"Every artist here was already vouched in by the community — if that trust is "
"enough for you, turn this on to embed any link an artist submits, "
"immediately, with no allowlist check and no AI review at all (the settings "
"below are skipped entirely while this is on). Off by default. Only enable "
"this if you are comfortable that a bad actor who made it through admission "
"could embed a link to anything."
msgstr ""
"Every artist here was already vouched in by the community — if that trust is "
"enough for you, turn this on to embed any link an artist submits, "
"immediately, with no allowlist check and no AI review at all (the settings "
"below are skipped entirely while this is on). Off by default. Only enable "
"this if you are comfortable that a bad actor who made it through admission "
"could embed a link to anything."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:884
msgid "Trusted embed platforms"
msgstr "Trusted embed platforms"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:890
msgid ""
"One hostname per line. A submitted link becomes a rich embed immediately if "
"it matches one of these (or a subdomain of one) — no AI review needed, no "
"network request made to the link itself."
msgstr ""
"One hostname per line. A submitted link becomes a rich embed immediately if "
"it matches one of these (or a subdomain of one) — no AI review needed, no "
"network request made to the link itself."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:894
msgid "Let artists submit other links too (AI-reviewed)"
msgstr "Let artists submit other links too (AI-reviewed)"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:899
msgid ""
"When enabled, a link to a site not on the trusted list above is not simply "
"discarded: the destination page is fetched and reviewed by your configured "
"AI provider (Settings → AI Providers) against the categories below before "
"deciding whether to embed it. If the AI cannot be reached, the request times "
"out, or the page cannot be safely fetched, the link is not embedded — it "
"fails safe. When disabled (the default), only the trusted platforms above "
"are ever embedded."
msgstr ""
"When enabled, a link to a site not on the trusted list above is not simply "
"discarded: the destination page is fetched and reviewed by your configured "
"AI provider (Settings → AI Providers) against the categories below before "
"deciding whether to embed it. If the AI cannot be reached, the request times "
"out, or the page cannot be safely fetched, the link is not embedded — it "
"fails safe. When disabled (the default), only the trusted platforms above "
"are ever embedded."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:903
msgid "Block pornographic / sexually explicit content"
msgstr "Block pornographic / sexually explicit content"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:908 includes/Admin/Settings.php:926
msgid "Only takes effect when AI review (above) is enabled."
msgstr "Only takes effect when AI review (above) is enabled."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:912
msgid "Block primarily commercial / promotional sites"
msgstr "Block primarily commercial / promotional sites"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:917
msgid ""
"Online stores, advertising, marketing landing pages. Off by default — an "
"artist linking to a shop selling their own prints is common and not "
"inherently unwanted. Only takes effect when AI review (above) is enabled."
msgstr ""
"Online stores, advertising, marketing landing pages. Off by default — an "
"artist linking to a shop selling their own prints is common and not "
"inherently unwanted. Only takes effect when AI review (above) is enabled."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:921
msgid "Block gambling / betting sites"
msgstr "Block gambling / betting sites"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:930
msgid "Additional disallowed categories"
msgstr "Additional disallowed categories"

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:935
msgid ""
"Optional — describe any other kind of content the AI should reject, in plain "
"language (e.g. \"hate speech or violent extremist content\", \"phishing or "
"scam pages\"). Only takes effect when AI review (above) is enabled."
msgstr ""
"Optional — describe any other kind of content the AI should reject, in plain "
"language (e.g. \"hate speech or violent extremist content\", \"phishing or "
"scam pages\"). Only takes effect when AI review (above) is enabled."

#: includes/Admin/Settings.php:941
msgid "Node label"
msgstr "Node label"

